wfRsvpDelete.name: wfRsvpDelete
wfRsvpDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete Rsvp.

wfRsvpDisable.name: wfRsvpDisable
wfRsvpDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable Rsvp.

wfRsvpSoloistSlots.name: wfRsvpSoloistSlots
wfRsvpSoloistSlots.description: Slot mask for which slot(s) RSVP Soloist is eligible to run on. The MSBit represents slot 1, the next most significant bit represents slot 2, and so on... Slots can be 1-14. Default is all slots on a BCN.

wfRsvpInfoLogFilter.name: wfRsvpInfoLogFilter
wfRsvpInfoLogFilter.description: Turn RSVP log ON or OFF for RSVP informational and warning messages. The bit position is used to represent a RSVP module: RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfRsvpDebugLogFilter.name: wfRsvpDebugLogFilter
wfRsvpDebugLogFilter.description: Turn RSVP log ON or OFF for RSVP debugging messages. The bit position is used to represent a RSVP module: RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfRsvpTraceLogFilter.name: wfRsvpTraceLogFilter
wfRsvpTraceLogFilter.description: Turn RSVP log ON or OFF for RSVP trace messages. The bit position is used to represent a RSVP module: RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfRsvpTotalSenders.name: wfRsvpTotalSenders
wfRsvpTotalSenders.description: The total number of Sender (PATH) states in the router.

wfRsvpTotalReservations.name: wfRsvpTotalReservations
wfRsvpTotalReservations.description: The total number of Reservation (RESV) states in the router.

wfRsvpTotalReserved.name: wfRsvpTotalReserved
wfRsvpTotalReserved.description: The total number of of successful reservations.

wfRsvpCurrentSoloistSlot.name: wfRsvpCurrentSoloistSlot
wfRsvpCurrentSoloistSlot.description: The Current RSVP Soloist slot. Slots can be 1-14. Default is zero.

wfRsvpSessionTable.name: wfRsvpSessionTable
wfRsvpSessionTable.description: Statistics concerning the sessions seen by a given system.

wfRsvpSessionEntry.name: wfRsvpSessionEntry
wfRsvpSessionEntry.description: Statistics concerning a single RSVP session seen by a given system.

wfRsvpSessionDestAddr.name: wfRsvpSessionDestAddr
wfRsvpSessionDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSessionDestAddrLength.name: wfRsvpSessionDestAddrLength
wfRsvpSessionDestAddrLength.description: The CIDR prefix length of the session address, which is 32 for IP4 host and multicast ad- dresses. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSessionProtocol.name: wfRsvpSessionProtocol
wfRsvpSessionProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSessionPort.name: wfRsvpSessionPort
wfRsvpSessionPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSen- derProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSessionSenders.name: wfRsvpSessionSenders
wfRsvpSessionSenders.description: The number of senders currently known to be part of this session.

wfRsvpSessionReceivers.name: wfRsvpSessionReceivers
wfRsvpSessionReceivers.description: The number of reservations being requested of this system for this session.

wfRsvpSessionRequests.name: wfRsvpSessionRequests
wfRsvpSessionRequests.description: The number of reservation requests this system is sending upstream for this session.

wfRsvpSenderTable.name: wfRsvpSenderTable
wfRsvpSenderTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by senders in PATH messages.

wfRsvpSenderEntry.name: wfRsvpSenderEntry
wfRsvpSenderEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single sender's PATH message.

wfRsvpSenderDestAddr.name: wfRsvpSenderDestAddr
wfRsvpSenderDestAddr.description: The destination IP address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderAddr.name: wfRsvpSenderAddr
wfRsvpSenderAddr.description: The source address used by this sender in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderDestAddrLength.name: wfRsvpSenderDestAddrLength
wfRsvpSenderDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderAddrLength.name: wfRsvpSenderAddrLength
wfRsvpSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderProtocol.name: wfRsvpSenderProtocol
wfRsvpSenderProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderDestPort.name: wfRsvpSenderDestPort
wfRsvpSenderDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSen- derProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderPort.name: wfRsvpSenderPort
wfRsvpSenderPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSenderPro- tocol is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpSenderHopAddr.name: wfRsvpSenderHopAddr
wfRsvpSenderHopAddr.description: The address used by the previous RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

wfRsvpSenderHopLih.name: wfRsvpSenderHopLih
wfRsvpSenderHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle used by the pre- vious RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

wfRsvpSenderInterface.name: wfRsvpSenderInterface
wfRsvpSenderInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this PATH message was most recently received.

wfRsvpSenderTSpecRate.name: wfRsvpSenderTSpecRate
wfRsvpSenderTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as rsvpSenderTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed rsvpSen- derTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.name: wfRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate
wfRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpSenderTSpecBurst.name: wfRsvpSenderTSpecBurst
wfRsvpSenderTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.name: wfRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU
wfRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

wfRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.name: wfRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU
wfRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

wfRsvpSenderInterval.name: wfRsvpSenderInterval
wfRsvpSenderInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as ad- vertised by the Previous Hop. UNITS milliseconds

wfRsvpSenderRSVPHop.name: wfRsvpSenderRSVPHop
wfRsvpSenderRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

wfRsvpSenderLastChange.name: wfRsvpSenderLastChange
wfRsvpSenderLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this PATH mes- sage; This is either the first time it was re- ceived or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

wfRsvpSenderPSBTimeout.name: wfRsvpSenderPSBTimeout
wfRsvpSenderPSBTimeout.description: The remaining lifetime of this sender's PSB.

wfRsvpSenderPolicy.name: wfRsvpSenderPolicy
wfRsvpSenderPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecBreak.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecBreak
wfRsvpSenderAdspecBreak.description: The global break bit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. If TRUE, at least one non-IS hop was detected in the path. If FALSE, no non-IS hops were detected.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount
wfRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.description: The hop count general characterization parame- ter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

wfRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw
wfRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.description: The path bandwidth estimate general character- ization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency
wfRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.description: The minimum path latency general characteriza- tion parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpSenderAdspecMtu.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecMtu
wfRsvpSenderAdspecMtu.description: The composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Guaranteed Ser- vice fragment. If FALSE or noValue, the ADSPEC does not contain a Guaranteed Service fragment.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak.description: If TRUE, the Guaranteed Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the guaranteed service. If FALSE, and rsvpSen- derAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGuaranteedSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'C' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'D' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'C' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'D' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMinLatency.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMinLatency
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMinLatency.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuch- Value indicates one of the following condi- tions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMtu.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMtu
wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSMtu.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the com- posed Maximum Transmission Unit general charac- terization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Controlled Load Service fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Controlled Load Service frag- ment.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLBreak.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLBreak
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLBreak.description: If TRUE, the Controlled Load Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the controlled load service. If FALSE, and wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLHopCount.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLHopCount
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLHopCount.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLPathBw.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLPathBw
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLPathBw.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMinLatency.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMinLatency
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMinLatency.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the minimum path latency general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuch- Value indicates one of the following condi- tions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMtu.name: wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMtu
wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLMtu.description: If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the com- posed Maximum Transmission Unit general charac- terization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfRsvpSenderAdspecCLSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpResvTable.name: wfRsvpResvTable
wfRsvpResvTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by receivers in RESV messages.

wfRsvpResvEntry.name: wfRsvpResvEntry
wfRsvpResvEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed by a single receiver's RESV message concerning a single sender.

wfRsvpResvDestAddr.name: wfRsvpResvDestAddr
wfRsvpResvDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvSenderAddr.name: wfRsvpResvSenderAddr
wfRsvpResvSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes in- dicates 'all senders'. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvDestAddrLength.name: wfRsvpResvDestAddrLength
wfRsvpResvDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvSenderAddrLength.name: wfRsvpResvSenderAddrLength
wfRsvpResvSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvProtocol.name: wfRsvpResvProtocol
wfRsvpResvProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvDestPort.name: wfRsvpResvDestPort
wfRsvpResvDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfRsvpResvProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvPort.name: wfRsvpResvPort
wfRsvpResvPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfRsvpResvProto- col is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvHopAddr.name: wfRsvpResvHopAddr
wfRsvpResvHopAddr.description: The address used by the next RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfRsvpResvHopLih.name: wfRsvpResvHopLih
wfRsvpResvHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle received from the previous RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfRsvpResvInterface.name: wfRsvpResvInterface
wfRsvpResvInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently received.

wfRsvpResvService.name: wfRsvpResvService
wfRsvpResvService.description: The QoS Service classification requested by the receiver.

wfRsvpResvTSpecRate.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecRate
wfRsvpResvTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as wfRsvpResvTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed wfRsvpResvTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate
wfRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvTSpecBurst.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecBurst
wfRsvpResvTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pac- ing is at the network's option. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpResvTSpecMinTU.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecMinTU
wfRsvpResvTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

wfRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU
wfRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

wfRsvpResvTSpecLevel.name: wfRsvpResvTSpecLevel
wfRsvpResvTSpecLevel.description: If the service is predictive or controlled- delay, this is the service level that is being requested. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

wfRsvpResvRSpecRate.name: wfRsvpResvRSpecRate
wfRsvpResvRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfRsvpResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Other- wise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvRSpecSlack.name: wfRsvpResvRSpecSlack
wfRsvpResvRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfRsvpResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpResvInterval.name: wfRsvpResvInterval
wfRsvpResvInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as ad- vertised by the Next Hop. UNITS milliseconds

wfRsvpResvScope.name: wfRsvpResvScope
wfRsvpResvScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length. If the length is non-zero, this contains a series of IP4 or IP6 addresses.

wfRsvpResvShared.name: wfRsvpResvShared
wfRsvpResvShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.

wfRsvpResvExplicit.name: wfRsvpResvExplicit
wfRsvpResvExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.

wfRsvpResvRSVPHop.name: wfRsvpResvRSVPHop
wfRsvpResvRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

wfRsvpResvLastChange.name: wfRsvpResvLastChange
wfRsvpResvLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this reserva- tion request; This is either the first time it was received or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

wfRsvpResvRSBTimeout.name: wfRsvpResvRSBTimeout
wfRsvpResvRSBTimeout.description: The remaining lifetime of this reservation's RSB.

wfRsvpResvPolicy.name: wfRsvpResvPolicy
wfRsvpResvPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfRsvpResvFwdTable.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTable
wfRsvpResvFwdTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in RESV messages.

wfRsvpResvFwdEntry.name: wfRsvpResvFwdEntry
wfRsvpResvFwdEntry.description: Information describing the state information displayed upstream in an RESV message concern- ing a single sender.

wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddr.name: wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddr
wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddr.name: wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddr
wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes in- dicates 'all senders'. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength.name: wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength
wfRsvpResvFwdDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength.name: wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength
wfRsvpResvFwdSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdProtocol.name: wfRsvpResvFwdProtocol
wfRsvpResvFwdProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdDestPort.name: wfRsvpResvFwdDestPort
wfRsvpResvFwdDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfRsvpResvFwdProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdPort.name: wfRsvpResvFwdPort
wfRsvpResvFwdPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfRsvpResvFwdProto- col is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpResvFwdHopAddr.name: wfRsvpResvFwdHopAddr
wfRsvpResvFwdHopAddr.description: The address used by the next RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfRsvpResvFwdHopLih.name: wfRsvpResvFwdHopLih
wfRsvpResvFwdHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle received from the previous RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfRsvpResvFwdInterface.name: wfRsvpResvFwdInterface
wfRsvpResvFwdInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently received.

wfRsvpResvFwdService.name: wfRsvpResvFwdService
wfRsvpResvFwdService.description: The QoS Service classification requested by the receiver.

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecRate.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecRate
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as wfRsvpResvFwdTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pac- ing is at the network's option. UNITS, bytes

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecLevel.name: wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecLevel
wfRsvpResvFwdTSpecLevel.description: If the service is predictive or controlled- delay, this is the service level that is being requested. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecRate.name: wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecRate
wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfRsvpResvFwdService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Other- wise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack.name: wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack
wfRsvpResvFwdRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfRsvpResvFwdService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.UNITS, microseconds

wfRsvpResvFwdInterval.name: wfRsvpResvFwdInterval
wfRsvpResvFwdInterval.description: The interval between refresh messages as ad- vertised by the Next Hop.

wfRsvpResvFwdScope.name: wfRsvpResvFwdScope
wfRsvpResvFwdScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length. If the length is non-zero, this contains a series of IP4 or IP6 addresses.

wfRsvpResvFwdShared.name: wfRsvpResvFwdShared
wfRsvpResvFwdShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.

wfRsvpResvFwdExplicit.name: wfRsvpResvFwdExplicit
wfRsvpResvFwdExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.

wfRsvpResvFwdRSVPHop.name: wfRsvpResvFwdRSVPHop
wfRsvpResvFwdRSVPHop.description: If TRUE, the node believes that the previous IP hop is an RSVP hop. If FALSE, the node be- lieves that the previous IP hop may not be an RSVP hop.

wfRsvpResvFwdLastChange.name: wfRsvpResvFwdLastChange
wfRsvpResvFwdLastChange.description: The time of the last change in this reserva- tion request; This is either the first time it was received or the time of the most recent change in parameters.

wfRsvpResvFwdPolicy.name: wfRsvpResvFwdPolicy
wfRsvpResvFwdPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfRsvpResvFwdStatus.name: wfRsvpResvFwdStatus
wfRsvpResvFwdStatus.description: 'valid' for all active RESV messages. This object may be used to install static RESV in- formation or delete RESV information.

wfRsvpIfEntry.name: wfRsvpIfEntry
wfRsvpIfEntry.description: A description of an RSVP interface

wfRsvpIfDelete.name: wfRsvpIfDelete
wfRsvpIfDelete.description: Indicates whether this RSVP If record is to be deleted or created

wfRsvpIfEnable.name: wfRsvpIfEnable
wfRsvpIfEnable.description: Indicates whether this RSVP intf record is to be enabled or disabled

wfRsvpIfState.name: wfRsvpIfState
wfRsvpIfState.description: The current state of the RSVP interface. Invalid indicates an error in processing the cfg record

wfRsvpIfCct.name: wfRsvpIfCct
wfRsvpIfCct.description: The circuit number of this RSVP interface

wfRsvpIfUdpNbrs.name: wfRsvpIfUdpNbrs
wfRsvpIfUdpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP UDP Encapsulation.

wfRsvpIfIpNbrs.name: wfRsvpIfIpNbrs
wfRsvpIfIpNbrs.description: The number of neighbors perceived to be using only the RSVP IP Encapsulation.

wfRsvpIfNbrs.name: wfRsvpIfNbrs
wfRsvpIfNbrs.description: The number of neighbors currently perceived; this will exceed wfRsvpIfIpNbrs + wfRsvpIfUdpNbrs by the number of neighbors using both encapsulations.

wfRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.name: wfRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple
wfRsvpIfRefreshBlockadeMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'Kb', Which is the minimum number of refresh intervals that blockade state will last once entered.

wfRsvpIfRefreshMultiple.name: wfRsvpIfRefreshMultiple
wfRsvpIfRefreshMultiple.description: The value of the RSVP value 'K', which is the number of refresh intervals which must elapse (minimum) before a PATH or RESV message which is not being refreshed will be aged out.

wfRsvpIfTTL.name: wfRsvpIfTTL
wfRsvpIfTTL.description: The value of SEND_TTL used on this interface for messages this node originates. If set to zero, the node determines the TTL via other means.

wfRsvpIfRefreshInterval.name: wfRsvpIfRefreshInterval
wfRsvpIfRefreshInterval.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface. UNITS milliseconds

wfRsvpIfRouteDelay.name: wfRsvpIfRouteDelay
wfRsvpIfRouteDelay.description: The approximate period from the time a route is changed to the time a resulting message ap- pears on the interface. UNITS hundredths of a second

wfRsvpIfUdpRequired.name: wfRsvpIfUdpRequired
wfRsvpIfUdpRequired.description: If TRUE, manual configuration forcees the use of UDP ncapsulation on the interface. If FALSE, UDP encapsulation is only used if wfrsvpIfUdpNbrs is not zero.

wfRsvpNbrTable.name: wfRsvpNbrTable
wfRsvpNbrTable.description: Information describing the Neighbors of an RSVP system.

wfRsvpNbrEntry.name: wfRsvpNbrEntry
wfRsvpNbrEntry.description: Information describing a single RSVP Neigh- bor.

wfRsvpNbrAddress.name: wfRsvpNbrAddress
wfRsvpNbrAddress.description: The IP4 or IP6 Address used by this neighbor. This object may not be changed when the value of the RowStatus object is 'valid'.

wfRsvpNbrProtocol.name: wfRsvpNbrProtocol
wfRsvpNbrProtocol.description: The encapsulation being used by this neigh- bor.

wfRsvpNbrCct.name: wfRsvpNbrCct
wfRsvpNbrCct.description: The circuit number of the interface where the neighbor is learned

wfRsvpNbrStatus.name: wfRsvpNbrStatus
wfRsvpNbrStatus.description: 'valid' for all neighbors. This object may be used to configure neighbors. In the presence of configured neighbors, the implementation may (but is not required to) limit the set of valid neighbors to those configured.

wfSRsvpDelete.name: wfSRsvpDelete
wfSRsvpDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete Static Rsvp.

wfSRsvpDisable.name: wfSRsvpDisable
wfSRsvpDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable Static Rsvp.

wfSRsvpState.name: wfSRsvpState
wfSRsvpState.description: The current state of Static Rsvp.

wfSRsvpSoloistSlot.name: wfSRsvpSoloistSlot
wfSRsvpSoloistSlot.description: Slot for which slot Static RSVP Soloist is eligible to run on. Slots can be 1-14.

wfSRsvpInfoLogFilter.name: wfSRsvpInfoLogFilter
wfSRsvpInfoLogFilter.description: Turn Static RSVP log ON or OFF for informational and warning messages. There is only RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfSRsvpDebugLogFilter.name: wfSRsvpDebugLogFilter
wfSRsvpDebugLogFilter.description: Turn Static RSVP log ON or OFF for debugging messages. The bit position is used to represent a RSVP module: RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfSRsvpTraceLogFilter.name: wfSRsvpTraceLogFilter
wfSRsvpTraceLogFilter.description: Turn RSVP log ON or OFF for RSVP trace messages. The bit position is used to represent a RSVP module: RSVP_LOG_RIF_PROCESSING 0x0001 - RIF processing. RSVP_LOG_SOLO_PROCESSING 0x0002 - SOLO processing. RSVP_LOG_ROUTE_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0004 - ROUTE interface processing. RSVP_LOG_MERGE_PROCESSING 0x0008 - MERGE processing. RSVP_LOG_DB_PROCESSING 0x0010 - database access processing. RSVP_LOG_INTSERV_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0020 - INTSERV interface processing. RSVP_LOG_CRM_INTF_PROCESSING 0x0040 - CRM interface processing. RSVP_LOG_STATIC_RSVP 0x0080 - STATIC RSVP processing. RSVP_LOG_CONTROL_PROCESSING 0x0100 - CONTROL processing. RSVP_LOG_MAP_VEC_PROCESSING 0x0200 - MAP VECTOR processing. RSVP_LOG_PROXY_PROCESSING 0x0400 - RSVP MIB PROXY processing. RSVP_LOG_REFRESH_PROCESSING 0x0800 - Path/Resv Refresh processing.

wfSRsvpRefreshInterval.name: wfSRsvpRefreshInterval
wfSRsvpRefreshInterval.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given STATIC PATH or STATIC RESV message. UNITS milliseconds

wfSRsvpTotalSenders.name: wfSRsvpTotalSenders
wfSRsvpTotalSenders.description: The total number of Static Sender (PATH) states in the router.

wfSRsvpTotalReservations.name: wfSRsvpTotalReservations
wfSRsvpTotalReservations.description: The total number of Static Reservation (RESV) states in the router.

wfSRsvpSenderTable.name: wfSRsvpSenderTable
wfSRsvpSenderTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by senders statically configured.

wfSRsvpSenderEntry.name: wfSRsvpSenderEntry
wfSRsvpSenderEntry.description: Information describing the state information used to create a sender thru configuration.

wfSRsvpSenderCreate.name: wfSRsvpSenderCreate
wfSRsvpSenderCreate.description: Whether to Delete this sender PSB

wfSRsvpSenderEnable.name: wfSRsvpSenderEnable
wfSRsvpSenderEnable.description: Whether to Disable this Sender PSB

wfSRsvpSenderStatus.name: wfSRsvpSenderStatus
wfSRsvpSenderStatus.description: Whether this Static PSB is valid or not

wfSRsvpSenderNumber.name: wfSRsvpSenderNumber
wfSRsvpSenderNumber.description: The number of this static sender. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

wfSRsvpSenderDestReplicate.name: wfSRsvpSenderDestReplicate
wfSRsvpSenderDestReplicate.description: Number of sessions for which this static path state should be replicated. For each replication, wfSRsvpSenderDestAddr will be incremented by one.

wfSRsvpSenderReplicate.name: wfSRsvpSenderReplicate
wfSRsvpSenderReplicate.description: Number of senders for which this static path state should be replicated. For each replication, wfSRsvpSenderAddr will be incremented by one.

wfSRsvpSenderIntegrity.name: wfSRsvpSenderIntegrity
wfSRsvpSenderIntegrity.description: The contents of the integrity object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfSRsvpSenderDestAddr.name: wfSRsvpSenderDestAddr
wfSRsvpSenderDestAddr.description: The destination IP address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderAddr.name: wfSRsvpSenderAddr
wfSRsvpSenderAddr.description: The source address used by this sender in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderDestAddrLength.name: wfSRsvpSenderDestAddrLength
wfSRsvpSenderDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderAddrLength.name: wfSRsvpSenderAddrLength
wfSRsvpSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderProtocol.name: wfSRsvpSenderProtocol
wfSRsvpSenderProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderDestPort.name: wfSRsvpSenderDestPort
wfSRsvpSenderDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by rsvpSen- derProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderPort.name: wfSRsvpSenderPort
wfSRsvpSenderPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by RsvpStaticSenderPro- tocol is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpSenderHopAddr.name: wfSRsvpSenderHopAddr
wfSRsvpSenderHopAddr.description: The address used by the previous RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

wfSRsvpSenderHopLih.name: wfSRsvpSenderHopLih
wfSRsvpSenderHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle used by the pre- vious RSVP hop (which may be the original sender).

wfSRsvpSenderInterface.name: wfSRsvpSenderInterface
wfSRsvpSenderInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this PATH message was most recently received.

wfSRsvpSenderTimeValue.name: wfSRsvpSenderTimeValue
wfSRsvpSenderTimeValue.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface. UNITS milliseconds

wfSRsvpSenderTSpecRate.name: wfSRsvpSenderTSpecRate
wfSRsvpSenderTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as RsvpStaticSenderTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed rsvpSen- derTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower. UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.name: wfSRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate
wfSRsvpSenderTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpSenderTSpecBurst.name: wfSRsvpSenderTSpecBurst
wfSRsvpSenderTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. UNITS, bytes

wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.name: wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU
wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.name: wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU
wfSRsvpSenderTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

wfSRsvpSenderPolicy.name: wfSRsvpSenderPolicy
wfSRsvpSenderPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspec.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspec
wfSRsvpSenderAdspec.description: If TRUE, an adspec is sent, if FALSE, no adspec is sent.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecBreak.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecBreak
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecBreak.description: The global break bit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. If TRUE, at least one non-IS hop was detected in the path. If FALSE, no non-IS hops were detected.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecHopCount.description: The hop count general characterization parame- ter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecPathBw.description: The path bandwidth estimate general character- ization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMinLatency.description: The minimum path latency general characteriza- tion parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, microseconds

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMtu.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMtu
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecMtu.description: The composed Maximum Transmission Unit general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present UNITS, bytes

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains a Guaranteed Ser- vice fragment. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contain a Guaranteed Service fragment.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSBreak.description: If TRUE, the Guaranteed Service fragment has its 'break' bit set, indicating that one or more nodes along the path do not support the guaranteed service. If FALSE, and wfSRrsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, the 'break' bit is not set. If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns FALSE or noSuchValue.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCtot.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'C' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDtot.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the end-to-end composed value for the guaranteed service 'D' parameter. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the fol- lowing conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSCsum.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'C' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bytes

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSDsum.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the composed value for the guaranteed ser- vice 'D' parameter since the last reshaping point. A return of zero or noSuchValue indi- cates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, microseconds

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSOverrides.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSOverrides
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSOverrides.description: If TRUE, the ADSPEC contains general parameter overrides for guaranteed service. If FALSE, the ADSPEC does not contains guaranteed service overrides. Note, if TRUE, ALL override parameters will be included and must be specified.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSHopCount.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the hop count general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following conditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue.

wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw.name: wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw
wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSPathBw.description: If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is TRUE, this is the service-specific override of the path bandwidth estimate general characterization parameter from the ADSPEC. A return of zero or noSuchValue indicates one of the following con- ditions: the invalid bit was set the parameter was not present If wfSRsvpSenderAdspecGSSvc is FALSE, this returns zero or noSuchValue. wfSRsvpResvTable.name: wfSRsvpResvTable
wfSRsvpResvTable.description: Information describing the state information displayed by statically configured reservation.

wfSRsvpResvEntry.name: wfSRsvpResvEntry
wfSRsvpResvEntry.description: Information describing the state information used to statically configure a reservation.

wfSRsvpResvCreate.name: wfSRsvpResvCreate
wfSRsvpResvCreate.description: Whether to Delete this RESV RSB

wfSRsvpResvEnable.name: wfSRsvpResvEnable
wfSRsvpResvEnable.description: Whether to Disable this RESV RSB

wfSRsvpResvStatus.name: wfSRsvpResvStatus
wfSRsvpResvStatus.description: 'valid' for all active RESV messages. This object may be used to install static RESV in- formation or delete RESV information.

wfSRsvpResvNumber.name: wfSRsvpResvNumber
wfSRsvpResvNumber.description: The number of this static resv. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and has no relation to any protocol value.

wfSRsvpResvDestReplicate.name: wfSRsvpResvDestReplicate
wfSRsvpResvDestReplicate.description: Number of sessions for which this static path state should be replicated. For each replication, wfSRsvpResvDestAddr will be incremented by one.

wfSRsvpResvReplicate.name: wfSRsvpResvReplicate
wfSRsvpResvReplicate.description: Number of senders for which this static path state should be replicated. For each replication, wfSRsvpResvAddr will be incremented by one.

wfSRsvpResvIntegrity.name: wfSRsvpResvIntegrity
wfSRsvpResvIntegrity.description: The contents of the integrity object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.

wfSRsvpResvDestAddr.name: wfSRsvpResvDestAddr
wfSRsvpResvDestAddr.description: The destination address used by all senders in this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvSenderAddr.name: wfSRsvpResvSenderAddr
wfSRsvpResvSenderAddr.description: The source address of the sender selected by this reservation. The value of all zeroes in- dicates 'all senders'. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvDestAddrLength.name: wfSRsvpResvDestAddrLength
wfSRsvpResvDestAddrLength.description: The length of the destination address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvSenderAddrLength.name: wfSRsvpResvSenderAddrLength
wfSRsvpResvSenderAddrLength.description: The length of the sender's address in bits. This is the CIDR Prefix Length, which for IP4 hosts and multicast addresses is 32 bits. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvProtocol.name: wfSRsvpResvProtocol
wfSRsvpResvProtocol.description: The IP Protocol used by this session. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvDestPort.name: wfSRsvpResvDestPort
wfSRsvpResvDestPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a destina- tion port for all senders in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfSRsvpResvProtocol, is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a virtual destination port number. A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvPort.name: wfSRsvpResvPort
wfSRsvpResvPort.description: The UDP or TCP port number used as a source port for this sender in this session. If the IP protocol in use, specified by wfSRsvpResvProto- col is 50 (ESP) or 51 (AH), this represents a generalized port identifier (GPI). A value of zero indicates that the IP protocol in use does not have ports. This object may not be changed when the value of the Status object is 'valid'.

wfSRsvpResvFilterSpecNum.name: wfSRsvpResvFilterSpecNum
wfSRsvpResvFilterSpecNum.description: For SE reservation style, this is the number of filter specs. For WF and FF styles, this is ignored. If SE style, there must be wfSRsvpResvFilterSpecNum SenderAddr and SenderPort entries where SenderPort 'j' is used by SenderAddr 'j'.

wfSRsvpResvHopAddr.name: wfSRsvpResvHopAddr
wfSRsvpResvHopAddr.description: The address used by the next RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfSRsvpResvHopLih.name: wfSRsvpResvHopLih
wfSRsvpResvHopLih.description: The Logical Interface Handle received from the previous RSVP hop (which may be the ultimate receiver).

wfSRsvpResvInterface.name: wfSRsvpResvInterface
wfSRsvpResvInterface.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which this RESV message was most recently received.

wfSRsvpResvTimeValue.name: wfSRsvpResvTimeValue
wfSRsvpResvTimeValue.description: The value of the RSVP value 'R', which is the minimum period between refresh transmissions of a given PATH or RESV message on an interface. UNITS milliseconds

wfSRsvpResvService.name: wfSRsvpResvService
wfSRsvpResvService.description: The QoS Service classification requested by the receiver.

wfSRsvpResvTSpecRate.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecRate
wfSRsvpResvTSpecRate.description: The Average Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Within a transmission burst, the ar- rival rate may be as fast as wfSRsvpResvTSpec- PeakRate (if supported by the service model); however, averaged across two or more burst in- tervals, the rate should not exceed wfSRsvpResvTSpecRate. Note that this is a prediction, often based on the general capability of a type of codec or particular encoding; the measured average rate may be significantly lower. UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate
wfSRsvpResvTSpecPeakRate.description: The Peak Bit Rate of the sender's data stream. Traffic arrival is not expected to exceed this rate at any time, apart from the effects of jitter in the network. If not specified in the TSpec, this returns zero or noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpResvTSpecBurst.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecBurst
wfSRsvpResvTSpecBurst.description: The size of the largest burst expected from the sender at a time. If this is less than the sender's advertised burst size, the receiver is asking the network to provide flow pacing beyond what would be provided under normal circumstances. Such pac- ing is at the network's option. UNITS, bytes

wfSRsvpResvTSpecMinTU.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecMinTU
wfSRsvpResvTSpecMinTU.description: The minimum message size for this flow. The policing algorithm will treat smaller messages as though they are this size.

wfSRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU
wfSRsvpResvTSpecMaxTU.description: The maximum message size for this flow. The admission algorithm will reject TSpecs whose Maximum Transmission Unit, plus the interface headers, exceed the interface MTU.

wfSRsvpResvTSpecLevel.name: wfSRsvpResvTSpecLevel
wfSRsvpResvTSpecLevel.description: If the service is predictive or controlled- delay, this is the service level that is being requested. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.

wfSRsvpResvRSpecRate.name: wfSRsvpResvRSpecRate
wfSRsvpResvRSpecRate.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfSRsvpResvService, this is the clearing rate that is being requested. Other- wise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue. UNITS, bits per second

wfSRsvpResvRSpecSlack.name: wfSRsvpResvRSpecSlack
wfSRsvpResvRSpecSlack.description: If the requested service is Guaranteed, as specified by wfSRsvpResvService, this is the delay slack. Otherwise, it is zero, or the agent may return noSuchValue.UNITS, microseconds

wfSRsvpResvScopeNum.name: wfSRsvpResvScopeNum
wfSRsvpResvScopeNum.description: The number of addresses in wfSRsvpResvScope. In the absence of the scope object, this should be zero

wfSRsvpResvScope.name: wfSRsvpResvScope
wfSRsvpResvScope.description: The contents of the scope object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length. If the length is non-zero, this contains a series of IP4 or IP6 addresses.

wfSRsvpResvShared.name: wfSRsvpResvShared
wfSRsvpResvShared.description: If TRUE, a reservation shared among senders is requested. If FALSE, a reservation specific to this sender is requested.

wfSRsvpResvExplicit.name: wfSRsvpResvExplicit
wfSRsvpResvExplicit.description: If TRUE, individual senders are listed using Filter Specifications. If FALSE, all senders are implicitly selected. The Scope Object will contain a list of senders that need to receive this reservation request for the purpose of routing the RESV message.

wfSRsvpResvPolicy.name: wfSRsvpResvPolicy
wfSRsvpResvPolicy.description: The contents of the policy object, displayed as an uninterpreted string of octets, including the object header. In the absence of such an object, this should be of zero length.
